Section C – Policy Conditions (continued)
3.
Premium Payments and Currency
All payments to or by the Company shall be made within the borders of the Republic of Kenya and in the
currency of the Republic of Kenya.
You
are required to pay the periodic premiums until the Maturity Date stated in the schedule. This is an
annual premium, but Equity Life allows you to pay in weekly, monthly, quarterly or half-yearly instalments.
Please note that all premium cheques must be written in favour of Equity Life Insurance Ltd. Cash must
only be paid directly to Equity Life offices or bank account and an official receipt obtained. Missed
premiums can be paid through M-PESA paybill No. xxxxx. The Company does not allow any of its agents
to receive cash on its behalf and shall accept no liability for monies paid to third parties and where such
money is not received and receipted by the Company.
4.
The period allowed for delayed premium payment
You are allowed a period of thirty (30) days (known as grace period) from the premium due date within
which you are required to make the regular payments after falling due. The policy will be in force during
the grace period and an
y beneﬁt arising will be p
ayable.
If you fail to pay a premium within thirty (30) days of the premium due date, the following will apply:
•
If less than two (2) full year’s periodic premiums have been paid, your policy will lapse and you will
forfeit all
beneﬁts
under the policy unless you reinstate the policy as provided for in clause 6 of this
section.

Reinstatement
Should you reduce or discontinue periodic premiums on this policy,
We

Our

provided that you pay all premiums in arrears, with interest thereon and that you comply with the
conditions we specify. We may require satisfactory evidence of your health, occupation and pursuits at that
point.
7.
Waiting period
Death and disability
beneﬁts
arising out of natural causes from the date your policy starts or from the

In the event an increase of cover is granted or a policy is reinstated following your request, the waiting

evidence of insurability.

13.
Policy Cash Surrender Value
This policy, if in force, shall have a cash/surrender value equivalent to the fund value
, accrued using the
minimum guaranteed interest rate specified. The life cover will automatically cease on surrender.
14.
Policy Loans
Policy loan are available on this policy
after 12 months from commencement of the policy
15.
Residence and Travel
You and all other insured lives must be permanently resident in the Republic of Kenya or East Africa as at
the commencement of cover. The
beneﬁts
in respect of claims will not be paid for an insured life that is
permanently resident in a foreign country except if they commenced the policy while still permanently
resident in the Republic of Kenya or East Africa.
In this case,
beneﬁts
are payable in Kenya Shillings so long as full premiums have been paid to date. There
are no travel restrictions.
16.
Misstated Age
If your age is misstated, the
beneﬁts
payable shall be adjusted based on the actual premiums paid and
the correct age. If the actual age is outside the limits of the product, the policy will be automatically voided
and
We
will refund premiums paid by you, less administration charges.

Section D – Endorsements
During the time this policy is in force (active), the Policyholder can request Us in writing to make the
following amendments or alterations to this policy:
1.
Change of payment frequency
–
Only at anniversary
2.
Addition/removal of guardian or child
–
Anytime in the life of the policy
3.
Change of contact details
No other changes to the policy are allowed, including but not limited to changes to the premium, term
and sum assured, except corrections of mistakes of wrongly captured data, misinformation or
misstatement of facts.
Section E – Deﬁnitions
1.
Policy Document - shall mean policy wording and the policy schedule.
2.
You
–
shall mean the policy owner/holder.
3.
Us/we
–
shall mean Equity Life.
4.
Life Assured
–
shall normally be the policy owner/holder.
5.
Accident - shall refer to an event whose happening or cause is unexpected and occurred through
violent, external and visible means.
6.
Accidental Death - shall mean death arising from bodily injury caused solely and directly by
violent, external, accidental and visible means and that such injury was the sole cause of death.
All other causes of death relating to illness, disease or the ageing process, shall be deemed to be
caused by natural causes.
7.
Accidental Disability
–
shall mean bodily injury resulting solely and directly from an accident
caused by outward violent and visible means which shall directly and independent of any other
cause result within three (3) months in disablement of the life assured.
8.
Loss of a limb - shall mean the loss by amputation or the total and permanent loss of use of an entire
hand or arm or an entire foot or leg solely and directly as a result of an accident as de
ﬁ
ned above.
9.
Loss of sight - shall mean total and irrecoverable loss of sight of one or both eyes.
10.
Permanent total disability and permanently and totally disabled - mean the insured is unable to
engage in any gainful occupation or employment for compensation, income or pr
oﬁt
for which the
insured is reasonably
qualiﬁed
by education, training or experience for the remainder of his or her
life.
11.

–
shall be the
ﬁr

ﬁr

where the proposal or application form for the policy has been received and approved by
Equity Life. However, in respect of premiums paid in cheque, bankers order or direct debit instructions,
the policy shall commence once the proposal or application form for the policy has been received.

The Company
–
refers to Equity Life Assurance Limited Kenya.
